<br>
Last time some people forgot their money.  This is understandable (so don't think Im throwing stones at you), I know you just probably woke up, said, &quot;Shoot, I got to get to SRO for PoH.&quot;  Then there you was without any money.<br>
<br>
However, this does bring up a serious issue though, Larr who took money out of his own pocket to buy these stones ended up short money.  We compensated him a diamond which he was happy with, however I still think this is unfair.  We are not a single guild whereas getting the funds maybe a little easier or we don't have a treasury.  And I'm not about to have someone lose money on these plane trips.<br>
<br>
So we are left with the following options:<br>
<br>
If you don't bring your 50pp, you don't go into the planes.<br>
<br>
Bring a druid that isn't going, charge those that forget a TP fee (maybe 20pp) and have that druid provide transportation to and from a portal close to a bank.<br>
<br>
Charge everyone a little bit more (75pp) any funds in excess will be lottoed at the end of the night (or something).<br>
- Don't like this idea though, people may just get lazy and not bring it, and all of a sudden we have only one person bringing 75pp.<br>
<br>
Also Im thinking of maybe charging a little more, so we can buy extra PoH stones just in case we have to do an extra Teleport, such as we all fail to break in.  Then at the end of the event we lotto the extra PoH stones.<br>
<br>
*********************************************************<br>
<br>
I would like to hear any suggestions or comments you may have regarding this.<br>
<br>
*********************************************************<br>
<br>
Also, I would like to thank those when I said we was short that donated extra platinum.  It was very nice, and it showed me that we had alot of decent people attending the raid.<br>
<br>
